messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why are Japanese fan content creators so much more strict about their activities in order to avoid copyright issues than Western fan creators? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Japanese fan content creators are often more strict about avoiding copyright issues because of the cultural differences and legal landscape in Japan. In Japan, respecting and protecting intellectual property rights is highly valued and deeply ingrained in their society. This means that Japanese fans are more cautious about using copyrighted material without permission to avoid legal consequences and out of respect for the creators. In the Western culture, there is a more relaxed approach towards intellectual property, with a focus on transformative and fair use, allowing fans to create content without facing severe legal consequences. So, the difference lies in cultural values and legal systems that influence how fan creators approach copyright issues.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: When I put pressure on my eyes for an extended period of time I see really cool patterns that alternate. What is that? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When you put pressure on your eyes for a long time, you might see cool patterns because you are affecting the way your eyes work. Our eyes have a special part called the retina that helps us see. When you press on your eyes, it puts pressure on the retina, and it gets a little confused. This confusion can make you see different colors and shapes that move or change. It's like when you press on a TV screen, the picture gets distorted. It's important not to press on your eyes too hard, though, as it can be harmful.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why does the shower water become hotter when someone flushes the toilet? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When you flush the toilet, two things happen at the same time. Firstly, water rushes down the toilet drain, and secondly, more water from the pipes flows to refill the toilet tank. This sudden demand for water can temporarily lower the amount of hot water available for the shower. As a result, the shower water becomes hotter because less cold water is being mixed with the hot water. It's like having a big glass of juice and adding more water to it; the juice becomes less diluted and stronger. Similarly, when someone flushes the toilet, the shower water becomes hotter because there is less cold water mixed in.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Hospital Fetal Heart rate and Cervix Monitors Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: In hospitals, doctors and nurses use special machines to monitor the heart rate of a baby inside a mommy's tummy. They also use another machine to check how open the mommy's cervix is. These machines help the doctors and nurses keep an eye on the baby's health and make sure everything is going well. The heart rate monitor listens to the baby's heartbeat to make sure it is strong and healthy. The cervix monitor helps the doctors know if the mommy's body is ready for the baby to be born. It's like a way to check if the baby is doing okay and if the mommy is ready to have the baby.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How does a state minimum wage increase impact people? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When a state increases the minimum wage, it means that the lowest amount of money people can legally be paid for their work goes up. This is good news for many people because it helps them earn more money to support themselves and their families. When the minimum wage increases, people who were earning less will now make more money for the work they do. This extra money can help them buy more things they need, like food and clothes. It can also make them feel happier and more secure because they have more money to take care of themselves and their loved ones.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How does a contagion spread from contact with an open wound to the target organ in the body ? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
When you get a cut or open wound, your body's defense system tries to heal it by sending special cells called white blood cells to the injured area. However, sometimes harmful germs can enter the wound and cause an infection. These germs are like tiny bugs that can make you sick. 

If the infection spreads, it means the germs start moving from the wound towards other parts of your body. Your body has a network of tiny tubes called blood vessels that carry blood to all your organs. When the infection spreads, the germs can hitch a ride through these blood vessels and reach different organs. This can make you feel even sicker, which is why it's important to keep wounds clean and protected!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why do aeroplanes/airplanes have headlights? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Airplanes have headlights, just like cars, to help them see and be seen in the dark. When we drive a car at night, we turn on the headlights so that we can see the road and other cars. It's the same for airplanes. They also need to see where they are going and make sure they don't run into anything.

Airplane headlights are usually located on the wings or near the nose of the plane. They have special bright lights that can illuminate the runway or any other obstacles in their path. This helps pilots land the plane safely and navigate on the ground.

Besides helping the pilots see, headlights also make the airplane visible to other planes and ground vehicles. Just like when we walk outside at night and wear bright clothes, airplanes use lights to show their position and help others know where they are.

So, in simple terms, airplanes have headlights to see where they are going and to make sure others can see them too, just like cars!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: The difference between a parody and a satire Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Parody and satire are both forms of humor that make fun of something or someone, but they do it in slightly different ways. Imagine you have a toy car and you want to make a funny version of it.

A parody is like making a funny copy of the toy car. You might change the color, make it bigger or smaller, or add silly decorations. It's still a toy car, but it looks different and makes you laugh.

Satire, on the other hand, is like using the toy car to make fun of something else. You might use the toy car to show how silly or strange real cars can be. For example, if the toy car has a lot of buttons that don't do anything, you could be making fun of cars with too many unnecessary features.

So, parody is about making something funny by changing its appearance, while satire is about using something to criticize or make fun of something else. Both can be really funny, but they have different ways of doing it.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why do my grey hairs pop when pulled? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Grey hairs often appear more visible when pulled out because of their lack of pigment. Hair color is determined by a pigment called melanin, which is produced by cells called melanocytes. As we age, the production of melanin decreases, and eventually, some hair follicles stop producing melanin altogether, resulting in grey or white hair.

When you pull out a grey hair, you might notice it seems brighter or more noticeable against your natural hair color. This is because the grey hair lacks melanin, making it appear lighter in contrast to the surrounding hair. Picture it like a group of colorful blocks, and suddenly you remove one white block from the middle; it becomes more noticeable against the colorful ones.

It is important to note that pulling out grey hairs doesn't necessarily cause more grey hairs to grow. Hair growth is determined by the hair follicle, and plucking a grey hair won't affect the follicle's ability to produce melanin or influence the growth of future hairs.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why was the European Union created? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
The European Union (EU) was created to make countries in Europe work together peacefully and help them become stronger. Before the EU, there were many wars and conflicts between European countries, which caused a lot of harm and suffering. The leaders of these countries wanted to find a way to prevent another war from happening.

So, they decided to create the European Union. The EU is like a big club where countries in Europe can join and work together. By being in this club, countries can trade more easily with each other, which means people can buy and sell things across borders without many restrictions. This helps the economies of all countries involved.

The EU also allows people to travel freely between member countries, making it easier for families and friends to visit each other. It also promotes peace and cooperation among member countries, as they have to discuss and solve problems together.

Overall, the European Union was created to bring European countries closer together, promote peace, improve trade, and make life better for people living in Europe.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How can Brick and mortar retailers continue to exist with online competitors Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Brick and mortar retailers can continue to exist with online competitors by offering something special that online stores cannot provide. Imagine you want to buy a toy. When you go to a physical store, you get to touch and see the toy before buying it. You can ask questions and get help from friendly staff. Plus, you can take the toy home right away, without waiting for it to be delivered. Online stores, on the other hand, have a larger variety of toys to choose from and often lower prices. So, to stay competitive, physical stores can make the shopping experience more fun and enjoyable. They can organize events, have play areas, or offer special discounts. Additionally, they can provide excellent customer service, making sure you find what you need and have a great time shopping. Some stores also allow you to order online and pick up your items in-store, combining the convenience of online shopping with the advantages of physical stores. With these strategies, brick and mortar retailers can still be successful even with online competitors.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: In US, when a city is divided into two states, if a crime occurs in a part of city and the criminal is caught in different part of city, Is he also violated Federal Interstate laws? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
If a city is divided into two states in the US, it means that part of the city falls within one state, and the other part falls within a different state. Now, if a crime happens in one part of the city, and the person who committed the crime is caught in the other part of the city, it could involve federal interstate laws.

You see, each state has its own laws to handle crimes that happen within its borders. However, when a crime crosses state lines, it becomes a federal matter. So, if the criminal committed a crime in one state and was caught in another state, they could be violating federal interstate laws.

The reason for this is that the federal government has the power to enforce laws that apply to the entire country, including crimes that happen between different states. It helps maintain order and ensures that criminals cannot simply escape from one state to another to avoid punishment.

So, in summary, if a criminal commits a crime in one part of a city divided between two states and is caught in the other part, they could potentially be violating federal interstate laws.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why are PIN codes not needed for online transactions? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
PIN codes are not needed for online transactions because online payments are made using your credit or debit card details, which already have important security measures in place. When you make an online payment, you enter your card number, expiration date, and a special code called the CVV number, which is usually found on the back of your card. These details help verify that you are the rightful owner of the card.

Additionally, online transactions often require an extra layer of security called "3D Secure" or "Verified by Visa" (for Visa cards) and "Mastercard SecureCode" (for Mastercard). These are like secret passwords that you set up with your bank, and they add an extra step to the payment process. When you make an online purchase, you may be redirected to your bank's website to enter this password, ensuring that only you can complete the transaction.

Overall, PIN codes are more commonly used for in-person purchases, where you physically insert or swipe your card. Online transactions have their own security measures to protect your information and ensure safe payments.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: what's an API? (computers) Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
An API, short for Application Programming Interface, is like a messenger that helps different computer programs talk to each other and share information. Imagine you and your friend want to play a game together, but you both speak different languages. You need someone to translate your messages so that you can understand each other, right? That's what an API does!

In the computer world, programs often need to talk to each other and share information, just like you and your friend. But they might be written in different languages or use different formats. An API acts as a translator that takes requests from one program, converts them into a language that another program can understand, and then sends back the response.

For example, when you use a mobile app to login with your Facebook account, the app uses Facebook's API to ask for your username and password. The API checks if the details are correct and sends back a response to the app, allowing you to log in. APIs make it easier for different programs to work together and share information without needing to know all the technical details of each other.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why do i sleep better when its cold? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
When it's cold, our bodies naturally feel more relaxed and cozy. This is because cooler temperatures help your body produce a hormone called melatonin, which helps you fall asleep and stay asleep. Think of melatonin as a little sleepy signal that tells your body it's time to rest.

When it's warm, your body might feel sweaty and uncomfortable, making it harder to relax and fall asleep. But when it's cold, your body temperature drops a bit, making you feel more comfortable and relaxed. Just like how a warm blanket or a cuddly teddy bear can make you feel safe and sleepy, cooler temperatures in your room can do the same.

Another reason is that colder temperatures reduce distractions. When it's hot, you might feel thirsty, sweaty, or hear buzzing sounds from fans or air conditioners. But when it's cold, there are fewer distractions, allowing you to focus on falling asleep peacefully.

So, when it's cold, your body produces more melatonin, you feel cozy and relaxed, and there are fewer distractions – all of these things help you sleep better!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why can I hear a TV from another room, even if the volume is off? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
When you watch TV, the sound comes out as invisible waves called sound waves. These waves travel through the air and reach your ears, allowing you to hear the sound. Now, sometimes even if the volume is off, you can still hear the TV from another room. How does that happen?

Well, imagine you have a friend who is whispering. If you stand close to them, you can hear the whisper quite clearly. But if you move far away, you might still hear a little bit of the whisper, even though it's much quieter. That's because sound waves can travel through the air and reach your ears, even if they are not very strong.

Similarly, when the TV is on, sound waves are created and travel through the air. Even if the volume is low or off, some sound waves can still escape the TV and move into other rooms. These weak sound waves can travel through walls, doors, and even around corners, reaching your ears in another room and making it seem like you can hear the TV even though the volume is off.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How is mass extinction humans fault? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Mass extinction refers to the widespread disappearance of different plant and animal species on our planet. Humans are responsible for causing mass extinction in several ways. Imagine you live in a beautiful garden with many different types of plants and animals. Now, imagine that you start cutting down all the trees and plants in your garden. By doing this, you are destroying the homes of many animals, and they will have nowhere to live. Similarly, humans are cutting down forests and destroying habitats where animals live, causing them to die off.

Humans are also polluting the air, water, and land. Just like you need clean air to breathe, animals also need clean habitats to survive. Pollution makes it difficult for them to survive, leading to their extinction. Additionally, humans are hunting animals for their skins, bones, or other body parts, which means many animals are killed and cannot have babies to continue their species.

In summary, humans are causing mass extinction by destroying habitats, polluting the environment, and hunting animals. It is important for us to understand that we need to take care of our planet and all the living creatures on it to prevent further mass extinctions.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: What is an orchestral conductor doing, and how can everyone follow what he's doing regardless of what instrument they have? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
An orchestral conductor is like the boss of a big group of musicians who play different instruments together. Their job is to lead and guide the musicians to play the music in harmony. 

Imagine you are playing a game with your friends, and you are the leader. Your friends are spread out in different places, and you need to give them directions so that everyone can play together. The conductor does the same thing but with music!

The conductor stands in front of the musicians and uses a special stick called a baton. They move their hands and the baton in different ways to show the musicians how fast or slow to play, when to start or stop, and how loud or soft to be. They also use their face and expressions to show emotions in the music.

Even though the musicians have different instruments, they all watch the conductor very carefully. The conductor's movements and expressions help everyone stay together and play as a team. It's like a secret language that all the musicians understand, so they can follow the conductor's lead and create beautiful music together!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How come—when looking at the light produced on earth VIA satellite imagery, they are always yellow, when in fact, there are lights of all different colors being produced? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
When we look at satellite images of the Earth at night, the lights appear mostly yellow because of the way the images are captured and processed. The satellites that capture these images use special sensors called "radiometers" that are sensitive to certain wavelengths of light. These sensors are designed to capture the specific wavelengths of light that humans can see most clearly, which happen to be in the yellow-green part of the color spectrum.

The radiometers on satellites are not able to capture the full range of colors that exist in the lights produced on Earth. They are mainly focused on capturing the intensity or brightness of the light, rather than the exact color. So, although lights of different colors are being produced on Earth, the satellite imagery may not accurately represent these colors.

Additionally, the atmosphere can affect the colors of lights seen from space. When light passes through the atmosphere, it gets scattered and altered, making the lights appear more uniform and yellowish in satellite images.

So, while there are lights of different colors being produced on Earth, the limitations of the satellite sensors and the atmospheric effects result in the lights appearing mostly yellow in satellite imagery.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How do women's menstrual synchronize if they spend a lot of time together? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
When girls start having their periods, they experience something called the menstrual cycle. This is when their body prepares for the possibility of having a baby. During this cycle, a woman's body goes through different changes. Sometimes, girls and women who spend a lot of time together may notice that their periods happen around the same time. But why does this happen?

Well, our bodies are influenced by hormones, which are like messengers that tell our body what to do. When women spend a lot of time together, their bodies may react to each other's hormones. It's like their bodies are talking to each other without even knowing it! These hormones can help regulate the menstrual cycle and make it more synchronized.

But it's important to remember that not all women's periods will sync up. It's just something that can happen when women spend a lot of time together. And even if it happens, it doesn't mean they are the same or something is wrong. Our bodies are complex, and every woman's menstrual cycle is unique!

So, in simple terms, when women spend a lot of time together, their bodies can communicate through hormones and make their periods happen around the same time.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: the upcoming "dairy crisis"...Is the Dept of Agriculture really "required" to purchase milk from farmers? And what will they do with it once they buy it? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
The Department of Agriculture (USDA) is not actually "required" to purchase milk from farmers, but they have a program called the Dairy Product Price Support Program that allows them to buy surplus milk if the prices drop too low. They do this to support dairy farmers and stabilize the milk market.

Once the USDA buys the milk, they have a few options for what to do with it. One thing they can do is turn it into other dairy products like cheese, butter, or powdered milk. They can also donate the milk to food banks or schools, so that people who need it can have access to it.

Imagine you and your friends have a lemonade stand, but suddenly there are too many lemons and not enough people buying lemonade. So, to help you and your friends, your parents decide to buy some of the extra lemons. They might use the lemons to make lemon cakes or give them to other families who want to make lemonade. This way, they help you and others, and the lemons don't go to waste.

In a similar way, the Department of Agriculture helps farmers by buying their extra milk and finding ways to use it or give it to people who need it.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How do tunnel builders know where they are going? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Tunnel builders use special machines and tools to know where they are going. Imagine you have a toy car and you want to make a tunnel in your sandbox. First, you would draw a line on the ground to show where you want the tunnel to go. Tunnel builders do something similar, but on a much bigger scale.

They use a machine called a tunnel boring machine (TBM) that is like a big drill. This machine is guided by a computer system that tells it where to dig. The computer uses a map of the area and tells the machine which direction to go. It's like following a treasure map to find the buried treasure.

To make sure they are digging in the right place, the tunnel builders also use special sensors and lasers. These sensors monitor the ground and measure its movement. If they see any changes, it means they might be going off track, so they make adjustments to stay on the right path.

So, just like you follow a line while making a tunnel in your sandbox, tunnel builders use machines, computers, maps, and sensors to know where they are going and make sure they dig in the right place.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why do trained muscles get more volume rather than density? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
When we talk about muscles getting more volume rather than density, it means they appear bigger rather than more compact. Imagine playing with a box of building blocks. If you stack the blocks on top of each other, you can make a tall tower (volume), but it may not be very strong. However, if you put the blocks close together, the tower will be smaller but much stronger (density).

Similarly, when we exercise and train our muscles, they grow in size (volume) because the muscle fibers increase in number and get larger. This is like adding more blocks to a tower, making it taller. The more we train, the more blocks (muscle fibers) we add, making the tower (muscles) bigger.

But to make the muscles denser, we need to make the individual muscle fibers stronger and tighter. This happens when we do exercises that focus on using the muscles' full potential and strength, like lifting heavy weights. It's like squeezing the blocks together tightly, making the tower (muscles) more compact and strong.

So, when we train our muscles, they get bigger (volume) but to make them denser, we need to challenge them with exercises that make the muscle fibers stronger and more compact.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: what happened to the hole in the ozone? Did we fix it, is it still there, was it never that big of a threat? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
The hole in the ozone layer was a big problem, but we have made great progress in fixing it. The ozone layer is like a big blanket in the sky that protects us from the sun's harmful rays. In the 1970s and 1980s, scientists discovered that certain chemicals called chlorofluorocarbons (CFCs) were damaging the ozone layer.

Many countries came together and agreed to stop using these harmful chemicals. They created a treaty called the Montreal Protocol, which banned the production and use of CFCs. This was a big step in fixing the hole in the ozone.

Since then, the levels of harmful chemicals in the atmosphere have been decreasing. Scientists have observed that the hole in the ozone layer has been getting smaller. However, it is still there, and we need to keep working to fix it completely.

So, we have made progress and the hole is getting smaller, but it's not completely fixed yet. It was a big threat, but with everyone's efforts, we are working towards a healthier and safer ozone layer for our planet.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why did I just pay $250 for a passport with a 3-week turnaround, when a driver's license is $25 and take 30 minutes? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
You paid $250 for a passport because it is a special document that allows you to travel internationally. It's like a special ticket that lets you visit other countries. A driver's license, on the other hand, is a document that says you are allowed to drive a car in your own country. 

A passport is more expensive because it involves more steps and security measures to make sure it's genuine and safe. When you apply for a passport, the government needs to check your background, take your photo, and make sure all your information is correct. They also need to make sure you are who you say you are, so they may ask for additional documents like your birth certificate. This process takes time and costs money.

A driver's license, on the other hand, is simpler and quicker to obtain. It usually involves a simple test to make sure you know the rules of the road, and then they take your photo. Since it's just for driving in your own country, it doesn't require as many security checks as a passport.

So, even though it may seem expensive and time-consuming, a passport is important for traveling to different countries, while a driver's license is only needed for driving in your own country.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: What does growth mean in terms of a countries economy? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Growth in a country's economy means that the country is getting bigger and stronger, just like when you grow taller and stronger! It means that more people have jobs and can buy things, making the country richer. This helps everyone have a better life with more opportunities and things to enjoy.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: (As an American) Why is freedom of speech protected from the government, but not corporations? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Freedom of speech is protected from the government because it is a fundamental right in the United States. The government cannot stop you from expressing your opinions. However, corporations are private entities and have their own rules. They can limit your speech within their platforms, just like how your parents can set rules at home.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Why are people so drawn to shiny things like minerals and gems, especially to the point where they're used in things like fine jewelry and crowns? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: People are drawn to shiny things like minerals and gems because they look really pretty and catch our eyes easily. They are like nature's sparkly treasures. We use them in jewelry and crowns because they make us feel special and fancy when we wear them.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: The US has more youth playing soccer than any other nation in the world. Why don't we have our own Messi? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: While the US has many young soccer players, having a player like Messi requires various factors. Messi is from Argentina, a country where soccer is deeply ingrained in their culture, and they have a strong soccer development system. The US is still working on building a similar system to nurture talents like Messi.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Why are Saturday morning cartoons idealized? What’s so different about them as opposed to other days’ cartoons? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Saturday morning cartoons are idealized because they were a special treat for kids. On weekdays, we had school and other responsibilities, but on Saturdays, we could relax and enjoy our favorite shows. It was a time when all our favorite cartoons aired together, making it a unique and exciting experience.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Making cocaine from the coca leaf. Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Coca leaves are plants that grow in some parts of the world. Cocaine is a drug that is made from these leaves. To make cocaine, the leaves are first harvested, then they go through a process where chemicals are added. These chemicals change the leaves into a powder that people use to get high.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Why doesn't the United States FDA create a daily multivitamin they approve of? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: The FDA is responsible for making sure medicines and supplements are safe and effective. However, creating a daily multivitamin would require testing and approving thousands of different combinations, which would be time-consuming and costly. Instead, the FDA sets guidelines for companies to follow when making vitamins, so you can choose one that meets their standards.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Why are Dolphins considered to be smart/advanced? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Dolphins are considered smart because they have big brains like humans and can do clever things. They communicate with each other using special sounds and clicks. They can solve problems, learn new tricks, and even recognize themselves in a mirror! That's why they are known as advanced and smart creatures.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Why when you stare at a moving pattern for an extended period of time and then look up, why everything's wavy. Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When you stare at a moving pattern for a long time, it can tire out the cells in your eyes that help you see clearly. When you look away, these tired cells can send mixed signals to your brain, making things appear wavy or distorted for a short while, similar to when you spin around and feel dizzy afterward.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Why do we drink cow's milk instead of human milk? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: We drink cow's milk instead of human milk because cows are big and produce a lot of milk. People have been farming cows for a long time, so it's easier to get cow's milk. Also, cow's milk has nutrients that are good for our bodies, just like how human milk is good for babies.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: How come if I put a lot of pressure on my fingers or toes (i.e. rest my head on my hand) they go "numb" and lose all feeling? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When you put a lot of pressure on your fingers or toes, you are squeezing the blood vessels and nerves that are responsible for sending messages to your brain. Without enough blood and oxygen, the nerves cannot work properly, so you lose feeling in that area. When you release the pressure, the blood flow returns, and you start feeling again.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: Why are Americans more or less complacent with the income inequality in their country? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Americans may be more complacent with income inequality because they believe in the American Dream, which says that anyone can become successful through hard work. They may also think that some people deserve to be wealthier because they work harder or are more talented. However, others are less complacent because they see the negative effects of income inequality, such as limited opportunities and unfairness.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: How are brain aneurysms diagnosed and treated? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Brain aneurysms are diagnosed using special scans like an MRI or CT scan, which take pictures of the brain. If an aneurysm is found, doctors might decide to treat it in two ways: through surgery, where they fix the weak spot in the blood vessel, or through a less invasive procedure called coiling, where a tiny wire is used to block the aneurysm.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: when is space where there is nothing but emptiness, what do rocket engines thrust against that make them move forward? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When in space, there is no air or anything to push against, but rockets carry their own fuel. Inside the rocket engine, fuel is burned, creating hot gases that rush out of the back really fast. According to Newton's third law, for every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction. So, when the gases shoot out, the rocket moves forward in the opposite direction!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: LI5, the current patent controversy between the top tech companies Google, MSFT, Apple, etc. Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: The top tech companies like Google, Microsoft, and Apple sometimes argue about who owns the rights to certain inventions or ideas. They go to court to decide who gets the credit and money for these inventions. It's like when you and your friend both claim to have made the same cool drawing, and your teacher has to decide who made it first.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: I am confused about how many KB are in 1 MB. Some sources seem to say 1000 and others say 1024. Which is it? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: In computing, 1 kilobyte (KB) is often defined as 1024 bytes, and 1 megabyte (MB) is often defined as 1024 kilobytes. However, some people use the metric system, where 1 kilobyte is considered as 1000 bytes and 1 megabyte is considered as 1000 kilobytes. So, it depends on the context and the source you are referring to.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Cosplay; is it just done for an event? Does one wear their outfit on multiple, random occasions? Is it just made for the photos? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Cosplay is like dressing up as your favorite character from a movie, show, or game. People usually wear their outfits to events called conventions where lots of fans gather. But some cosplayers also wear their costumes outside of events, like to parties or when they hang out with friends. It's not just for photos, but people do take pictures to remember and share their awesome costumes. It's all about having fun and showing love for a character you really like!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why is mercury the chosen substance for determining the temperature? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Mercury is chosen for determining temperature because it expands when it gets hot and contracts when it gets cold. This expansion and contraction is easy to measure with a thermometer. Think of it like a balloon that gets bigger when you blow air into it and smaller when you let the air out. Mercury acts the same way, getting bigger or smaller depending on how hot or cold it is. This makes it a good substance for measuring temperature accurately. However, it's important to remember that mercury can be harmful, so we need to be careful when using it.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Would increasing the minimum wage and setting a maximum wage strengthen the middle class? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Increasing the minimum wage means that the lowest-paid workers would earn more money for their work. This could help them afford basic needs and improve their living conditions. However, setting a maximum wage means that no one can earn more than a certain amount. While this might seem fair, it could discourage people from working hard or taking risks to earn more money. Instead, it could lead to less innovation and investment in businesses. So, while increasing the minimum wage could support the middle class, setting a maximum wage might have unintended consequences and not necessarily strengthen it.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: "morning hands" Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: "Mornings hands" refers to the feeling we have in our hands when we wake up in the morning. Sometimes, when we sleep, our hands can get a bit stiff or numb. This happens because our body is relaxed and not moving much while we sleep, which can cause a temporary change in blood flow to our hands. When we wake up, it might take a little while for our hands to feel normal again. We can shake or move our hands gently to help get the blood flowing properly and make the feeling go away.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: During the Middle Ages, what would happen if a country invaded another, and the invaded country couldn't afford to fight so it surrendered, but the invading country kept on fighting? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: During the Middle Ages, if one country invaded another and the invaded country couldn't afford to keep fighting, they would surrender. Surrender means they would agree to stop fighting and accept defeat. However, sometimes the invading country didn't stop fighting even after the surrender. This was not fair or nice, but it happened. The invading country might continue fighting because they wanted more things from the invaded country, like land, money, or power. It was a difficult and scary time for the invaded country because they had to do their best to protect themselves and hope for help from other countries or allies.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why is cooking wine not regulated in stores like regular wine is? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Cooking wine is not regulated in stores like regular wine because it contains a high amount of salt and other additives, making it unsuitable for drinking. Regular wine is made to be enjoyed as a beverage, so it undergoes strict regulations to ensure its quality, taste, and safety. Cooking wine, on the other hand, is specifically made for adding flavor to dishes during cooking. Since it is not meant to be consumed directly, it doesn't need the same regulations. It's important to remember that drinking cooking wine can be harmful due to its high salt content, so it's best to use it only for cooking purposes.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: please ELI5 what the sound is when i put a cup near my ear Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When you put a cup near your ear, you hear a sound because the cup acts like a funnel for the noises around you. The cup collects the sound waves that are in the air and directs them into your ear. This makes the sound louder and clearer, so you can hear things that may be too quiet otherwise. It's similar to when you cup your hand around your ear to listen better. The cup helps to focus the sound waves into your ear, allowing you to hear more clearly.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why do lights and stars sometimes appear to have points sticking out of them? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Lights and stars sometimes appear to have points sticking out of them because of the way light travels through the Earth's atmosphere. When light passes through tiny particles in the air, like dust or water droplets, it gets scattered in different directions. This scattering can make the light appear to have points or spikes around it. It's similar to how a flashlight beam can look fuzzy or have rays when you shine it through a foggy window. So, when we see lights or stars with points, it's because their light is bouncing off these tiny particles in the air and creating that effect.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: In Sci-fi movies, why are alien organisms almost always silicone based? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: In sci-fi movies, alien organisms are often portrayed as silicone-based because it allows for imaginative possibilities. Silicone has some similar properties to carbon, which is the building block of life on Earth. It is flexible, can form complex structures, and withstand extreme conditions. However, silicone is not commonly found in living organisms on Earth. So, when it comes to creating aliens in movies, writers and artists can use silicone as a way to make these creatures seem different and exotic. It helps to spark our imagination and makes the aliens appear more alien-like to us.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why does smoking preserve food? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Smoking helps preserve food because it adds a special flavor and helps to prevent bacteria from growing. Smoke is made by burning wood or charcoal, and it contains tiny particles that can stick to the food. These particles have chemicals called antimicrobials that fight against bacteria and slow down their growth, making the food last longer. The smoke also dries out the food, removing moisture that bacteria need to survive. So, when we smoke food, it not only tastes delicious but also makes it safer to eat for a longer time.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How are those huge cranes that work on skyscrapers setup/made taller/moved to really high floors? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Those huge cranes that work on skyscrapers are made up of different sections that fit together like a puzzle. First, a smaller crane is used to assemble the base of the big crane on the ground. Then, each section is lifted up and attached to the previous one using the smaller crane. This process repeats until the crane reaches the desired height. To move the crane to higher floors, a part called a climbing frame is used. It's like an elevator for the crane, allowing it to climb up the building. So, bit by bit, the crane is built up and moved higher until it reaches the top of the skyscraper.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How can someone just walk away from a home loan? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Walking away from a home loan, also known as "defaulting," happens when someone can't afford to pay back the money they borrowed to buy their house. Imagine if you borrowed a toy from a friend and promised to give it back later. But if you find out that you can't pay for it or it's too expensive, you might have to give the toy back to your friend and say you can't keep it. It's the same with a home loan. When someone can't keep up with the payments, they have to give the house back to the bank, and the bank will try to sell it to someone else to get their money back.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How has the sloth been able to survive natural selection for millions of years without predators wiping out the species. Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Sloths have been able to survive for millions of years because they are really good at hiding and moving slowly. They spend most of their time hanging in trees, where they blend in with the leaves, making it hard for predators to see them. They also move so slowly that it's difficult for predators to even notice them. Sloths have long claws that help them grip onto trees, making it even harder for predators to catch them. Additionally, sloths have a special greenish fur that helps them camouflage in the trees. So, by being excellent hiders and moving slowly, sloths have been able to avoid predators and survive for a long time.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: What would happen if a male took female viagra? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
If a male were to take female Viagra, it may not have the same effect as it does on females. Female Viagra is a medication designed to increase blood flow and sensitivity in a woman's genital area. It helps women with sexual arousal issues. Males have different bodies and reproductive systems, so the medication may not work in the same way.

For males, there is a different medication called Viagra that helps with erectile dysfunction. This medication works by relaxing the blood vessels in a man's genital area, allowing more blood to flow there and helping him get an erection.

If a male takes female Viagra, it might not have any effect on him or might cause side effects that females may experience, like headaches or stomach problems. It's important to remember that medications should only be taken if prescribed by a doctor, as they know what is best for each person based on their specific health conditions.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why can certain types of batteries be recharged when others cannot? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Sure! Think of batteries like tiny energy containers. Some batteries are made of materials that can store and release energy over and over again, like a rechargeable battery. It's like having a cup that you can fill with water, drink it, and then fill it up again. These batteries are designed with special chemicals that can undergo a reversible reaction, which means they can easily convert chemical energy into electrical energy when you use them and convert it back when you recharge them.

On the other hand, there are non-rechargeable batteries that are made differently. They have chemicals that can only go through a one-way reaction. It's like having a bag of candy that you can only eat once, and you cannot refill it again. Once the chemicals in these batteries are used up, they cannot generate electricity anymore, and you have to throw them away.

Rechargeable batteries are more expensive upfront, but they are a better choice in the long run because you can use them many times by simply recharging them, saving money and reducing waste.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why can humans eat almost anything, yet so many foods like chocolate, grapes, and xylitol are dangerous for dogs and other mammals? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Humans have a special ability to eat a wide variety of foods because our bodies are designed to handle different types of nutrients. We have evolved over time to be able to digest and process a lot of things. However, other mammals, like dogs, have different bodies and digestive systems compared to us.

Some foods, like chocolate, grapes, and xylitol, can be harmful to dogs because their bodies cannot process these substances properly. For example, chocolate contains a substance called theobromine, which is safe for humans but can be toxic for dogs. Grapes contain a specific chemical that can cause kidney damage in dogs. Xylitol, a sweetener found in many sugar-free products, can cause a rapid drop in a dog's blood sugar level, leading to serious health problems.

So, even though these foods are safe for us, they can be dangerous for dogs and other mammals because their bodies are not built to handle them. That's why it's important to be careful and not share our food with our furry friends, to keep them safe and healthy.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How does the "brace" position in aircraft emergencies protect us? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
The "brace" position in aircraft emergencies is a special way we sit to protect ourselves. Imagine you are sitting on a chair, and suddenly the plane shakes and jerks a lot. In these situations, we need to be prepared for a bumpy landing or a sudden stop. 

To protect ourselves, we follow the "brace" position. We lean forward and put our hands on the seat in front of us, keeping our head down and tucked between our knees. This position helps to make our body small and compact, like a little ball. 

When we brace, it helps protect our head, neck, and spine. These are important parts of our body, and we want to keep them safe. By bending forward and covering our head, we reduce the chances of hitting anything hard if there's a sudden stop. It's like having a shield around our most vulnerable parts.

Remember, the brace position is just for emergencies, and most of the time, we don't need to worry about it when we fly. The flight attendants are there to guide us and help keep us safe if anything unexpected happens.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Is it possible to make an app that is a scale for an iPhone? Since we have pressure sensitive touch, is there a reason we can’t have it measure just how much pressure for small items? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Yes, it is possible to create an app that functions as a scale for an iPhone. However, there are some limitations to consider. The pressure-sensitive touch on an iPhone is designed to measure the force applied to the screen, but it is not accurate or sensitive enough to measure small items accurately.

To explain it like you're five: Imagine you have a scale at home to weigh fruits. When you put a heavy fruit on the scale, it tells you the correct weight because it is designed for that purpose. But if you try to weigh something very light, like a small piece of candy, the scale may not give you an accurate weight because it is not sensitive enough to measure such small things.

Similarly, the pressure-sensitive touch on an iPhone is made to detect fingers and gestures, not to accurately measure small items. It can tell if you press hard or soft on the screen, but it is not precise enough to measure the weight of small objects. So while an app can be created to simulate a scale, it won't be as accurate as a real scale designed specifically for measuring weight.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Gas octanes? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Gasoline octane ratings indicate the quality of gasoline. Think of it like a score that tells us how well the gasoline can resist knocking in your car's engine. Knocking is the sound you hear when the gasoline explodes too early in the engine. It's like when you try to blow up a balloon too fast and it makes that loud popping sound. 

Now, gasoline comes in different octane ratings, such as regular, mid-grade, and premium. Regular gasoline has the lowest octane rating, while premium has the highest. The higher the octane rating, the better the gasoline can resist knocking. 

Different cars need different octane ratings. Some cars have engines that are designed to run on regular gasoline, while others require premium. It's like how some toys need regular batteries, while others need special ones. 

So, when you go to the gas station with your parents, they choose the gasoline that matches their car's needs. They want to make sure the gasoline won't cause any knocking in the engine, so they pick the right octane rating.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why do you often feel to hot/cold when you want to sleep? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
When we want to sleep, our body tries to relax and get comfortable, just like when we are playing or doing other activities. But sometimes, our body temperature can affect how comfortable we feel. When you feel hot, it means your body is warmer than usual, and when you feel cold, your body is colder than it should be.

The reason you might feel too hot when you want to sleep is because your body is still producing heat, but you are covered with blankets or wearing too many clothes. Like a car engine, our bodies generate heat to keep us warm, and if we don't let that heat escape, it can make us feel too hot.

On the other hand, feeling cold when you want to sleep might happen if your body is not warm enough. This can occur if you are not covered with enough blankets or wearing warm pajamas.

So, to make sure you feel just right, it's important to find a balance. Make sure you have the right amount of blankets and clothes to keep you cozy but not too hot or too cold. That way, you can have a good night's sleep and feel comfortable!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How are games cracked? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Games are cracked by clever people who try to find a way to unlock the game without paying for it. Imagine you have a secret code lock on your toy box, and you need to enter the right numbers to open it. Similarly, games have a special code that only the people who made the game know, and you have to buy the game to get that code.

When someone cracks a game, they try to figure out the secret code without buying the game. It's like they become little detectives and search for a way to trick the game into thinking it's been paid for. They dig deep into the game's programming, exploring all the hidden corners to find any weak points.

Once they find a weak point, they create a special program called a crack. This crack fools the game into thinking it has been properly paid for, even if it hasn't. It's like creating a magic key that opens the toy box without needing to know the secret code.

But remember, it's important to support the game developers and buy games legally because they work hard to create these amazing experiences for us to enjoy!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why is Quebec still French speaking? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Quebec is still French-speaking because a long time ago, French explorers came to this land and settled here. They liked it so much that they decided to stay and build their homes. They spoke French, so they taught their children to speak French as well. As time went on, more and more people came from France to live in Quebec, and so the French language continued to be spoken and passed down from generation to generation.

Eventually, other people from different countries also came to live in Quebec, but the French-speaking people wanted to preserve their language and culture. They worked hard to protect and promote the French language by creating laws and programs to ensure that French remained the main language of Quebec.

Today, Quebec is still French-speaking because the people there are proud of their language and want to keep it alive. They have French schools, French-speaking TV shows and movies, and many signs and documents are also in French. So, even though other languages are spoken in Canada, Quebec remains unique as a place where French is the primary language.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: How do television stations know how many people are watching/ How do television ratings work? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Television stations want to know how many people are watching their shows so they can understand which shows are popular and which ones are not. They use a special system called television ratings to figure this out. 

Imagine you have a friend who loves to eat pizza. Your friend tells you about the different types of pizza they like, and you decide to try them too. This is similar to television ratings. To know what shows people are watching, a small group of people called a "sample" is chosen to represent the entire population. Just like you try different types of pizza, these people have a special box called a "television meter" attached to their TV. 

Whenever they watch a show, the meter knows which show it is. The television meter sends this information back to a company, like Nielsen, which collects all the data. This data is like your friend telling you which pizza they liked the most. The company then analyzes the data and calculates how many people are watching each show. This helps television stations decide which shows are popular and which ones they should keep or cancel.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: If nuclear waste is the biggest concern over the power plants, why couldn't/wouldn't we just launch the waste into space and into the sun to dispose of it? Or even just into space. Isn't there plenty of radiation there, already? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Nuclear waste is indeed a major concern when it comes to nuclear power plants. However, launching this waste into space or towards the sun isn't a practical solution for a few reasons.

Firstly, launching objects into space is extremely expensive. It requires powerful rockets and a lot of fuel, making it economically unviable. Sending nuclear waste into space would require countless launches, costing billions of dollars.

Secondly, launching nuclear waste into space poses significant risks. If a rocket carrying this waste were to fail or explode during launch, it could release radioactive material into the Earth's atmosphere, causing severe environmental and health consequences.

Lastly, while there is radiation in space, it is not concentrated in one place like nuclear waste. The radiation in space comes from various natural sources and is spread out, making it less harmful. Concentrated nuclear waste poses a greater threat if not handled and stored properly.

Instead of launching waste into space, scientists and engineers focus on developing safer methods for handling and storing nuclear waste on Earth. These methods include deep geological repositories, where waste is stored in carefully selected underground locations, ensuring long-term safety and containment.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: If there are concentration camps in North Korea that are similar to those found in Germany during WWII, why hasn't a military force such as NATO intervened? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
Concentration camps in North Korea, similar to those in Germany during WWII, are indeed a grave concern. However, it's important to understand that international intervention is a complex and delicate matter.

NATO, a military alliance of several countries, aims to ensure peace and security among its member nations. Intervening militarily involves numerous considerations. First, North Korea is a sovereign country, which means it has its own government and authorities. To intervene, NATO would need a strong reason, such as protecting its member countries or preventing a large-scale humanitarian crisis.

Furthermore, international interventions can be risky and have unintended consequences. North Korea possesses a powerful military and may retaliate, leading to a potentially devastating conflict. Additionally, intervention might harm the very people it intends to help, as it can be difficult to ensure their safety during such operations.

Instead, countries and organizations use other means to address the situation. Diplomatic efforts, economic sanctions, and international pressure are often employed to encourage change and advocate for human rights. These approaches aim to promote dialogue and peaceful resolutions while avoiding the severe consequences that military intervention might bring.

In summary, international intervention is a complex decision with significant risks and consequences. Efforts are made to address issues like concentration camps through diplomatic means, economic pressure, and international advocacy.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 150 words: Why does the law allow companies to purchase or merge with other companies? Why aren't all purchases/mergers viewed as a consolidation within an industry and a step closer to monopolization? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content:
The law allows companies to purchase or merge with other companies because it can bring several benefits. When companies combine, they can often achieve economies of scale, which means they can produce goods or services more efficiently and at a lower cost. This can lead to lower prices for consumers. Additionally, mergers or acquisitions can help companies expand into new markets or gain access to new technologies, leading to innovation and better products.

Not all purchases or mergers are viewed as a consolidation within an industry and a step closer to monopolization because there are laws in place to prevent monopolies. Monopolies occur when one company has complete control over a particular industry, which can lead to higher prices and reduced competition. To prevent this, there are antitrust laws that regulate mergers and acquisitions. These laws ensure that mergers do not create a dominant market position that would harm consumers or other businesses. Government agencies like the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) closely review mergers to ensure they do not violate antitrust laws.

In summary, while mergers and acquisitions can bring benefits, there are laws in place to prevent them from leading to monopolies and harming competition.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 50 words: What makes humans want to kiss one another? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When humans feel a special connection or love for someone, they may want to show it by kissing. Kissing can make people feel happy and closer to each other. It's a special way to show love, like a hug for the lips!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why do big bags of chips have zero trans fats but the smaller version of the exact same chips contains trans fats? Please explain like I'm five.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why do radio stations only end in odd numbers? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Radio stations in the United States traditionally end in odd numbers because it helps avoid interference between different stations. Imagine a group of friends playing different musical instruments in the same room. If they all play at the same time, it will sound messy and you won't be able to hear any specific instrument properly. Similarly, radio stations need their own space on the radio frequency spectrum to avoid overlapping and creating a jumble of signals. By using odd numbers, stations can maintain enough distance from each other, allowing listeners to tune into specific stations without interference.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: When a small child cries, they often start with the initial cry followed by a long-ish pause, and then they start crying again. Why the long pause? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: When a small child cries, they may experience a "long-ish pause" before crying again because they are trying to communicate their needs. Crying is their way of telling adults that they need help or attention. During the pause, they are observing and waiting for a response from their caregivers. They might be hoping that their parents or caregivers will come and comfort them or try to understand what they need. Babies and young children are learning how to express themselves, so the pause allows them to see if their cry is effective in getting the attention they need.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: - if pi is in between the number 3 and 4 how can it be infinite? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Pi (π) is a special number that represents the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter. Even though it is between 3 and 4, it has a unique property. Pi is what we call an irrational number, which means it cannot be expressed as a simple fraction or a finite decimal. The reason it is infinite is because its decimal digits go on forever without repeating in a pattern. Just like counting numbers can go on forever (1, 2, 3, 4, and so on), pi's decimal digits never stop. This makes it an interesting and important number in mathematics!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why is there so much focus on colonizing Mars and not an equal focus on colonizing the Moon? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: There is a lot of focus on colonizing Mars because it is more similar to Earth compared to the Moon. Mars has a thin atmosphere, which means it could potentially support human life with some modifications. It also has water ice, which is essential for us to survive. The Moon, on the other hand, doesn't have a significant atmosphere or water. Additionally, Mars has a day-night cycle similar to Earth's, while the Moon has extremely long days and nights. So, Mars offers more possibilities for us to live comfortably, while the Moon is mostly used for scientific research and could serve as a stepping stone for future Mars missions.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How penny bidding sites (like QuiBids or Beezid) make their money? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Penny bidding sites make money by selling bids. You see, when you want to bid on something, you have to buy these special bids first. Let's say you buy 100 bids for $1 each. Now, when you place a bid, the price of the item goes up by just a penny, but you have already spent one of your bids. So, even if you don't win the item, the site still keeps your bid money. And since many people are bidding on the same item, they end up spending lots of bids. So, even if the item sells for a low price, the site makes a profit from selling all those bids.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why is there so much apparent public criticism against labor unions when they empower mostly low to middle income workers; who make up the massive majority of workers? Please explain like I'm five.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How do you move? Please explain like I'm five.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why do doctors stop applying a defibrillator after a couple of tries? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Doctors stop applying a defibrillator after a couple of tries because the heart needs time to rest and recover. When a person's heart stops or is beating irregularly, a defibrillator sends an electric shock to restart it. However, using a defibrillator multiple times can be tiring for the heart and may cause more harm than good. Just like when we play a game and get tired, our bodies need a break to regain energy. So, doctors stop using the defibrillator after a few tries to give the heart a chance to rest and for them to explore other ways to help the person.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How does Southern and Northern US Border control work? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: The US has a border separating it from Mexico. This border is divided into two parts: the Southern Border and the Northern Border. Border control means making sure people and things coming into the US follow the rules. At the Southern Border, there are checkpoints and officers who check passports and ask questions to make sure people are allowed to enter. They also use technology like cameras and sensors to monitor the border. The Northern Border is a bit different. There are also checkpoints and officers, but people can cross more easily because the US and Canada have a friendly relationship. Both borders aim to keep the country safe and make sure everyone follows the rules.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How do brands manufacturing non-concentrated, natural fruit juice keep the taste constant? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Brands making non-concentrated, natural fruit juice ensure a consistent taste by using a special process. Firstly, they carefully select the ripest and juiciest fruits. Then, they squeeze the fruits to extract the juice, removing any seeds or pulp. Next, they quickly heat the juice for a short time to kill any harmful bacteria and preserve freshness. After that, they cool it down rapidly. Finally, they package the juice in airtight containers, protecting it from oxygen and light that can change the taste. This process helps maintain the delicious taste of the fruit juice, just like when you enjoy a fresh juice from the fruit itself.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why does water cause a near perfect hexagon bokeh on camera lenses? Please explain like I'm five.

message.content: Water causes a near perfect hexagon bokeh on camera lenses because of its shape and properties. When light passes through a camera lens, it gets bent or refracted. The shape of the lens and the aperture (the hole that lets light in) determine how the light is focused. When you take a photo with bright lights in the background, like streetlights or the sun, the light passes through tiny droplets of water in the air. These droplets act like tiny lenses themselves, bending the light and creating the hexagon shape. So, when you see those beautiful hexagon shapes in the background of a photo, you can thank the water droplets for that!

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: How does insane Clown Posey have such large following, who are willing to do anything for the band? Please explain like I'm five.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Why can you not see deleted comments with a permalink, but you can see deleted threads with one? Please explain like I'm five.

messages.content: Answer the following question no more than 100 words: Is burping/belching something you get better at with practice? Please explain like I'm five.
